This paper is primarily focused on the analysis of online tracking, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves large-scale data analysis and web crawling, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses country-specific differences in web tracking, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cybercrime (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to categorize websites, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
